commit.message: Moved the app-server and model-server back into the root folder of the project
Adding heroku steps to add buildpack to README
Moving node app related files to app-server, and model-serving app related files to model-server
Adding Procfile and ProcfileHoncho to help Heroku run multiple servers when it starts up. Also download and unpack the Roberta large  model
Updated the README with the part on how to install the python related dependencies i.e. pip install and downloading the roberta model
Replacing OC clothing related text with Code Butler text
Switched flask app to use Roberta large model instead of base (small) model
Fixed Git URL on README
Adding new AI related flow image to the README page
Fixing the bug that stopped the hard-coded questions from working
Replace O Clothing image with Code Butler flow
Fixed the API that passes questions to the Roberta model
Fixed a spelling mistake and also added a flask app
Added Basic Java questions
Amending the greetings for language proposed by Brian
Extend message further for unrecognised messages
Enabling the Advance mode questions
Adding the texts for languages not supported
Fixed the issue with our i18n, it now replaces embedded variables when values are passed in
Replaced i18n with our own version to overcome current issues
Saving current state: i18n is still problematic, clears off locales - needs further investigation
Fixed the bug by adding the case clause
Removed unnecessary locales and adding menus (languages)
Changing OCC to Code Butler
Replacing logos with Code butler logos
Removing yarn.lock as we are using npm.lock
Initial commits on the OC Clothing
